<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Sources">Sources</span></h2>
<p>Carian is known from these sources:<sup id="cite_ref-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-0"><span>[</span>1<span>]</span></a></sup></p>
<ul>
<li>Personal names with a suffix of -ασσις, -ωλλος or -ωμος in Greek records</li>
<li>Twenty inscriptions from <a href="/wiki/Caria" title="Caria">Caria</a> including four <a href="/wiki/Bilingual_inscription" title="Bilingual inscription">bilinguals</a></li>
<li>Inscriptions of the Caromemphites, an ethnic enclave at <a href="/wiki/Memphis,_Egypt" title="Memphis, Egypt">Memphis, Egypt</a></li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Graffiti" title="Graffiti">Graffiti</a> elsewhere in Egypt</li>
<li>Scattered inscriptions elsewhere in the Aegean world</li>
<li>Words stated to be Carian by ancient authors.</li>
</ul>
<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Description">Description</span></h2>
<table class="metadata plainlinks ambox mbox-small-left ambox-notice" style="">
<tr>
