<h3><span class="mw-headline" id="Principles">Principles</span></h3>
<p>Two features that help identify the language as Anatolian:<sup id="cite_ref-1" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-1"><span>[</span>2<span>]</span></a></sup></p>
<ul>
<li>Asigmatic nominative (without the <a href="/wiki/Indo-European_language" title="Indo-European language" class="mw-redirect">Indo-European</a> <a href="/wiki/Nominative_case" title="Nominative case">nominative</a> ending *-s) but -s for a <a href="/wiki/Genitive_case" title="Genitive case">genitive</a> ending: úśoλ, úśoλ-s</li>
<li>Similarity of basic words to other Anatolian languages: <i>ted</i> "father"; <i>en</i> "mother"</li>
</ul>
